<div id="review_1798986995" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1798986995" />
    <a title="Terry Madden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6562497-terry-madden"><img alt="Terry Madden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1399413695p2/6562497.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1798986995?book_show_action=true">Feb 16, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Terry Madden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Terry Madden" href="/user/show/6562497-terry-madden">Terry Madden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1798986995" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8349753983545910489">It&apos;s hard to believe that people like Black Elk lived through a span of history that so thoroughly crushed a way of life. He lived from the time of Lakota independence, with bison enough for all and the freedom to travel the land wherever they wished, to the horror of Wounded Knee and the end of a way of life. His story is a microcosm of native destiny. Very powerful reading.</span>
  <span id="freeText8349753983545910489" style="display:none">It's hard to believe that people like Black Elk lived through a span of history that so thoroughly crushed a way of life. He lived from the time of Lakota independence, with bison enough for all and the freedom to travel the land wherever they wished, to the horror of Wounded Knee and the end of a way of life. His story is a microcosm of native destiny. Very powerful reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8349753983545910489" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
